<DOC><DOCNO> AP890612-0182 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-12-89 2236EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-BusAccident     06-12 0232</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Bus Accident,0238</SECOND><HEAD>One Girl Dies, Nine Injured in Bus Accident</HEAD><DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A private school bus taking students home fromtheir first day in summer school collided with a truck Monday,killing one girl and injuring nine others.   The bus was carrying seventh- and eighth-grade girls attendingsummer classes at the Chinquapin School, a private preparatoryschool in the small community of Highlands, school secretary DebraHicks said.   One girl was killed in the accident at an intersection at about4:30 p.m., but Ms. Hicks did not know her age.   Emergency medical service officials said the injured _ ninestudents and three adults _ were transferred to several areahospitals. The drivers of the school bus, the truck and a motorcyclealso were hospitalized.   Three girls were in stable condition at San Jacinto MethodistHospital in nearby Baytown, hospital spokeswoman Jeanni Pruitt said.Two other girls taken to Sunbelt Regional Medical Center did nothave serious injuries, a hospital official said.   Three girls were taken to Doctors Hospital-East Loop, buthospital officials could not release any information about theirconditions.   Three adults and one student were taken to Hermann Hospital. Twoof the adults and the girl were in stable condition, and one adultwas in guarded condition, hospital spokeswoman Katherine Byard said.   Harris County Sheriff's officials did not have any immediatedetails about what caused the multi-vehicle accident.</TEXT></DOC>